,Recommended,296240,12085333,"Posted: 13 September, 2014",all,machinehuntress,"I expected nothing of the game when I picked it up for around two bucks in a sale, and yet got a cute and nice city-builder that kept me playing until I was finished with it. It was very addictive in its simplicy. It is not ""Banished"" or any of the other eleborate resource management sims, and much more simplified in gameplay, yet the mechanics are the same, of course. Gain Resource, use resource to build stuff, trade with others to gain money, upgrade your buildings and gear with it etc.You start out with 5 people and the goal is to find ""the spring of happiness"" To do so, you have to build your colony up to 50 people with all buildings purchased and upgraded. Which took me around 16 hours, with all (ingame) gold achievements collected. The comic style of the graphics is rather on the simple side, but fits well to the overall tone of the game. If you like these sort of games and search for something less stressful and punishing in regard of the resource management, you can do no wrong with picking up ""The Promised Land."" Especially when it is dirt-cheap in a sale.I had fun with it, for sure."
76561198008899722,Recommended,296240,13873427,"Posted: 6 January, 2015",all,DragonsDeck,"A very simple economy/city building game.  You get 'X' amount of people to do a bunch of chores, once you've collected enough resources, built the required buildings and accomplished a few tasks you get more people to get more resouces, build buildings and accomplish more tasks.There isn't exactly a whole lot of depth to it but what is there is fun and entertaining.  Some of the people are better at one task vs another, so you have to make descisions as who to stick where to make the best use of your people.  At the same time you have to manage their hunger and happiness, both of which are accomplished easily enough, but can be a bit of a pain if you haven't been stockpiling enough.  There is a few mini-games and such thrown in to give a bit of variety as well.Not exactly the prettiest looking game, but the art was charming enough and fit the gameplay.The game isn't very long, but is enjoyable enough to warrant a recomendation."
