76561198013130865,Recommended,296240,10592817,"Posted: 20 June, 2014",all,Adryan,"The Promised Land is a task-driven, casual strategy game that lets the player build a small colony from the ground up. There is no possibility of failure, no death, and no time pressure. Though not particularly challenging, it is still fun to see the colony grow.Clearly there was a lot of attention to detail from the designers. An interesting touch was that the minimap changes in portrait-like fashion as new buildings are added. Apart from the main story, there are mini-games in the form of physics puzzles where the player can use a cannon to shoot wooden structures to knock down pirates. Kids will probably enjoy this part the most.The game is a steal when under $5 dollars. One caution - the natives are depicted in a friendly, cartoonish way, but some may still find their images stereotyped and dated."
