76561197995459909,Recommended,296240,17755134,"Posted: 28 August, 2015",all,Tau,"*The Promised Land' is a casual city building game that works great of you just want some pet game to play for a day or two. The graphics are colourful and cartoonish, and very much reminds you of the sterotypical kids-games, but in a way that didn't bother me, at least. The colonist models are fairly diverse, and only repeated 2-3 times each among 50 colonists. The gameplay is easy enough to grasp, but has a certain pace to it that kept it interesting - despite a few instances of waiting for enough resources to tick in.The game, however, is also very liniar in the sense that your progression in the game comes from completing a number of quests. These quests do allow some level of ""free"" development through research, but ultimately limits the type of resources you can get, what buildings you can build and so on to the progress of the questline.The buildings are limited to fixed, preset locations, so the freedom to make your colony as you want is more or less non-existentThe 7,3 hours of gameplay I've had is a complete run with every challenge and in-game acheivement on the highest level.All in all I found the game enjoyable to play through, but with little to no replay value. It's probably well suited for people unfamiliar with city-building or management games as a first peak into the genre."
