,Recommended,296240,26601217,"Posted: 14 November, 2016",all,osirish,"I installed the game at 10pm, just to try it out as I was in the mood for a casual city (colony) builder.I finished the game at 9am the next morning! I just couldn't stop playing. That's the best recommendation I can give it.Pros.Graphics are cute and well detailed.The music ranges from good to beautiful.The sound effects suit the style.Extremely casual and relaxing game, no stress or pressure here!Over 10 hours of gameplay for a relatively cheap price.It scratched the ""city builder"" itch.Mini-games keep things fresh.Solid mobile port with no bugs.Simple to learn and understand.Cons.If you like big strategy city building games, you might be disappointed, everything is very basic, but done well.The are no screen resolutions in the options. Windowed or full screen.There's practically no way you can lose. No challenge?I was disappointed when I completed it (I wanted more! ... or is that a pro?)Very little replayability.Overall, there's a research tree, an economy, city building, and resource management but all very simple without a lot of depth and there are mini-games. The game, however, is addictive, keeps you interested and entertained, is extremely well presented, and is value for money. As a casual city builder, it hit all the right buttons. Good job Boolat Games!"
