76561198144593917,Recommended,296240,21011158,"Posted: 6 February, 2016",all,mikesanerd,"The Promised Land is a casual management game. You order your workers to gather and mine various resources, and then you use them to gradually build new things, unlock new areas of the map, and complete quests. It is vary similar to the Virtual Villagers games.The game is casual, to be sure, in that there is no real challenge or risks. But I got a lot of satisfaction from building up my city, and the game didn't require too much intense gameplay. It was a nice, relaxing game of simple pleasures. If you are looking for a management/building game where you don't have to agonize over decisions or stress out about optimizing everything, this may be a good game for you."
